WunderLINQ
The WunderLINQ requires a lot of permissions to enable all the cool features the app provides. On the next few screens we will explain the need for each permission request. You will only be presented with these screens this one time. If you need to enable certain permissions after, you will need to go into Android Settings and enable them. Select your preferred Navigation App. Level of WunderLINQ support varies, for more details see the following page: https://blackboxembedded.com/pages/integrations Thank you for purchasing the WunderLINQ! Ride Safe. Agree Disagree
WunderLINQ needs to run a Accessibility Service The WunderLINQ app uses an Accessibility service to enable Picture-in-Picture launching. WunderLINQ needs permissions to use your camera The WunderLINQ app needs access to your camera to take pictures and record video. WunderLINQ needs permissions to use your phone to make phone calls The WunderLINQ app needs access to phone to initiate calls. WunderLINQ needs permissions to use read your contacts The WunderLINQ app needs access to your contacts to list them for dialing. WunderLINQ needs permissions to record audio The WunderLINQ app needs access to your microphone to record video audio. WunderLINQ needs location permission The WunderLINQ app needs access to your location to allow background track recording and data logging. Location permission is also used for data points such as elevation, GPS speed, and bearing. WunderLINQ needs Bluetooth permission The WunderLINQ app needs the ability to connect to the WunderLINQ Hardware. WunderLINQ needs write permission The WunderLINQ app needs access to write files for track logging and photos. WunderLINQ needs phone state permission The WunderLINQ app needs phone state permissions for the cellular signal strength data point. WunderLINQ needs overlay permission The WunderLINQ app needs overlay permissions for background video recording. WunderLINQ needs notification access The WunderLINQ app needs notification access so that it can control your music player. Functionality limited Since location access has not been granted, this app will not be able to save waypoints or log your location. Since Bluetooth permission has not been granted, this app will not be able to connect to the WunderLINQ hardware. Since write access has not been granted, this app will not be able to save files. Since camera access has not been granted, this app will not be able to take photos or videos. Since contact access has not been granted, this app will not be able to display or call your contacts. Since phone access has not been granted, this app will not be able to place phone calls. Since microphone access has not been granted, this app will not be able to record videos. Since audio recording access has not been granted, this app will not be able to record videos. Since phone state access has not been granted, this app will not be able to display your signal strength. WunderLINQ needs usage stat access The WunderLINQ app needs access to usage stats for auto launch of the app when the WunderLINQ device is connected.
